<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12101h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12101h">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12101h"> 101(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> &mdash; p &mdash; </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Jacques Le Brigant, an eighteenth-century linguist. In his <cite>El&eacute;ments succints de la langue des celtes-gom&eacute;rites ou Bretons. Introduction &agrave; cette langue et, par elle, &agrave; celle de tous les peuples connus</cite> (1779), he argues that Breton is the mother of all tongues. Adding a p and rearranging the letters slightly will turn &lsquo;Keltomaniac&rsquo; <font color="green">[Celtomaniac]</font> into &lsquo;Kleptomaniac&rsquo;, parodying Le Brigant&apos;s ingenuity in assimilating unrelated words to Breton. </mm> </dd></dl>
